race.comment: You can always forgive a horse one bad run and, although she didn't beat a rival home last start, AFFAIRE VUE (9) might be able to bounce back here. She's fitter, she drops in grade and she's drawn low so expect to see her in the first few in running. She's got enough ability to win. HEAVENBENT (10) tackled some nice races and showed glimpses of above average ability in her first campaign in SA. She will improve on whatever she does first-up but she can run well. MELLIFLUENT (1) is third-up and wasn't beaten far in a stronger city race last time. He will be close to peak fitness third-up and is a definitely top three chance. BIG MAV (2) brings winning form and is a chance to go back-to-back, while BOLTED IN (4) ran well last time and might be ready to fire.
